section.def:
arbitrator
                (仲裁人) means an arbitrator appointed under any
            provision of these Rules;

chairman
                (主席) means the chairman of the arbitration
            panel;

claimant
                (申索人), in relation to a dispute being referred to
            arbitration, means the party making the claim;

clerk
                (書記) means the clerk to the arbitration panel
            referred to in section 4(6);

HKIAC
                (仲裁中心) means the Hong Kong International
            Arbitration Centre;

member
                (成員) means a member of the arbitration
            panel;
